---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const updated = 'April 9, 2026';
---

<BaseLayout title="Privacy Policy — Burdweiser.com" description="Privacy policy for burdweiser.com">
  <div class="container page-wrap">
    <div class="page-header">
      <div class="page-eyebrow">legal</div>
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="page-sub">Last updated: {updated}</p>
    </div>

    <div class="content prose">
      <p>
        This privacy policy describes how burdweiser.com ("the Site," "we," "us") handles information
        when you visit this website. We are committed to respecting your privacy and being transparent
        about our data practices.
      </p>

      <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
      <p>
        <strong>Information you provide voluntarily.</strong> The Site does not currently have user accounts,
        contact forms, or comment systems. We do not actively collect personal information from visitors.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Automatically collected information.</strong> When you visit the Site, basic technical
        information may be logged by our hosting provider (Cloudflare) as part of standard web server
        operations. This may include your IP address, browser type, pages visited, and referring URL.
        This data is used solely for security and operational purposes and is subject to
        <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/privacypolicy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Cloudflare's Privacy Policy</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>Cookies and Tracking</h2>
      <p>
        The Site uses a single functional cookie to remember your light/dark mode preference
        (stored in your browser's <code>localStorage</code>, not transmitted to any server).
        We do not use advertising cookies, tracking pixels, or third-party analytics services.
      </p>

      <h2>Third-Party Services</h2>
      <p>
        The Site is hosted on <strong>Cloudflare Pages</strong>. Cloudflare may process certain
        technical data as part of delivering the Site to you. Please refer to Cloudflare's privacy
        policy for details on their data handling practices.
      </p>
      <p>
        The Site loads fonts from <strong>Google Fonts</strong>. Google may collect limited data
        when fonts are requested. See
        <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google's Privacy Policy</a>
        for details.
      </p>
      <p>
        We do not use Google Analytics, Facebook Pixel, or any other behavioral tracking tools.
      </p>

      <h2>External Links</h2>
      <p>
        Posts on this Site may contain links to external websites. We are not responsible for
        the content or privacy practices of those sites. We encourage you to review the privacy
        policies of any external sites you visit.
      </p>

      <h2>Data Retention</h2>
      <p>
        We do not store personal data on our own systems. Any data retained by Cloudflare
        is subject to their data retention policies.
      </p>

      <h2>Your Rights</h2>
      <p>
        Since we do not collect or store personal information directly, there is no personal
        data to access, correct, or delete on our end. If you have questions about data processed
        by Cloudflare, please contact them directly.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this privacy policy from time to time. The date at the top of this page
        reflects the most recent revision. Continued use of the Site after any changes constitutes
        acceptance of the updated policy.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        If you have questions or concerns about this privacy policy, you can reach us via
        the contact information listed on the <a href="/about">About page</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page-wrap { padding-top: 0; max-width: 720px; }
  .page-header {
    padding: 48px 0 36px;
    border-bottom: 0.5px solid var(--border);
    margin-bottom: 36px;
  }
  .page-eyebrow {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--accent);
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }
  h1 {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 2rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: -0.5px;
    margin-bottom: 6px;
  }
  .page-sub {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 12px;
    color: var(--text3);
  }
  .content { padding-bottom: 64px; }
  strong { font-weight: 500; color: var(--text); }
  code {
    background: var(--bg2);
    border: 0.5px solid var(--border);
    padding: 1px 5px;
    border-radius: 3px;
    font-size: 0.85em;
  }
</style>
